<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-12-20T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-12-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="264" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d264">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72119/230f</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the <gloss type="to">Diplomatic Representatives in All
                                        Neutral Countries</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Circular telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-12-20">
                                        <hi rend="italic">December 20, 1916</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Department’s circular December 18 regarding peace.<note n="1" xml:id="d264fn1">The President’s communication of that date to
                                    the belligerent governments. <ref target="frus1916Supp#pg_97">
                                        <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1916, Supplement,
                                        pp. 97</ref>–<ref target="frus1916Supp#pg_99">99</ref>.</note> Please deliver quoted note to the Government
                                to which you are accredited for its information.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>